# 📊 Dashboard Usage Guide

## 🧠 Overview

This guide explains how to navigate and use the Enterprise BI 360 dashboard effectively across different business functions.

The dashboard is designed to provide a seamless experience for stakeholders across Finance, Sales, Marketing, Supply Chain, and Executive teams.

---

## 🏠 Home Page

- Acts as the central navigation hub
- Provides access to all business views
- Includes high-level KPIs and quick insights

---

## 💰 Finance View

- Focuses on profitability and revenue analysis
- Displays key financial KPIs such as Net Sales, Gross Margin, and Net Profit
- Used for financial performance tracking

---

## 📈 Sales View

- Analyzes customer, product, and regional performance
- Tracks sales growth and YoY performance
- Helps identify top-performing segments

---

## 📣 Marketing View

- Focuses on campaign and customer insights
- Provides visibility into customer behavior and engagement trends

---

## 🚚 Supply Chain View

- Tracks operational efficiency metrics
- Includes forecast accuracy and error analysis
- Helps optimize supply chain performance

---

## 🧭 Executive View

- High-level strategic dashboard
- Consolidates KPIs across all business functions
- Designed for quick decision-making

---

## ⚙️ Navigation System

- Built using bookmarks and buttons
- Enables seamless movement between report pages
- Ensures a smooth user experience without clutter

---

## 📌 Key Usage Principle

Start from the Home page → select a business function → apply filters → drill into details for deeper analysis.
